    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 57</em>, <em>Pathfinder #51: The Hungry Storm pg. 67</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 2 gp (common), <img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\"/> 10 gp (folding); <strong>Weight</strong> 8 lbs. (common), 12 lbs. (folding)</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>This tool lets you dig a pit at a rate of 2 cubic feet per minute. If a shovel is used in combat, treat it as a one-handed improvised weapon that deals bludgeoning damage equal to that of a club of its size.<br/><br/> <em>Folding Shovel</em>: A folding shovel is a full-sized shovel with a sturdy sectional handle that folds into pieces no longer than the shovel blade, allowing it to fit in a smaller space such as a backpack. Converting the shovel from its folded state to usable (or vice versa) is 2 full-round actions.</p>",
